<head ><name  type='ancientAuthor'>Thucydides</name></head>

<p ><name  type='ancientAuthor'>Thucydides</name> was an Athenian most famous for his history of the war between <placeName  key='Athens'>Athens</placeName> and <placeName  key='Sparta'>Sparta</placeName>, the <soCalled >Peloponnesian War</soCalled> (see also <name  n='History' type='ancientGenre'>History</name>). His life and work are both described briefly in the article <soCalled ><name  type='ancientAuthor'>Thucydides</name>.</soCalled></p>


